This condition needs checked first before the loop, right?  Otherwise you're priming the loop with an invalid index.

In practice, this probably works because I think npos is probably MAX_INT on most implementations, but we shouldn't rely on that.

I wonder if we should walk the string backwards, something like

inline std::string getResourceName(const std::string_view id){
while(id.rbegin() != id.rend() && std::isdigit(*id.rbegin())){
    id.remove_suffix(1);
}
if (id.rbegin() != id.rend() && *id.rbegin() == '_'){
   id.remove_suffix(1);
}
return {id};
}


Maybe is more clear and handles more edge cases?

It can be changed to:
return std::string{id};

